# SPLICE vs FireCut - Complete Feature Comparison
## Side-by-Side Analysis of Adobe Premiere Pro Plugins

**Date**: 2026-01-12
**SPLICE Version**: 6.0.3 (CEP + UXP)
**FireCut Version**: 1.2.4
**Analyst**: Forensic Code Analysis

---

## Executive Summary

**SPLICE** is a modern, well-architected video editing plugin with strong core features focused on podcast/creator workflows. It has **production-grade implementation** of silence cutting, takes detection, AI music generation, and animated captions.

**FireCut** is a mature, feature-rich plugin with **extensive AI integrations** including B-roll stock search (7 providers), advanced caption styling (15 color pickers), auto zoom with transcript sync, workflow automation, TTS, and comprehensive export formats.

### Quick Verdict

| Category | Winner | Reasoning |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| **Core Editing** | SPLICE | Better takes detection, multitrack support, J-cuts |
| **AI Features** | FireCut | More AI integrations (B-roll, zooms, chapters) |
| **Caption Styling** | FireCut | 15 color pickers, gradients, 6 animation types |
| **Music Generation** | TIE | Both use AI (Replicate), similar capabilities |
| **Workflow Automation** | FireCut | Multi-step pipelines with save/load |
| **Code Quality** | SPLICE | Clean, readable, non-obfuscated, modern patterns |
| **Security** | SPLICE | JWT auth, CSRF protection, server-side validation |
| **Architecture** | SPLICE | Railway + PostgreSQL + Redis, modern stack |

---

## Feature Comparison Matrix

### 1. Core Video Editing Features

| Feature | SPLICE | FireCut | Winner | Notes |
|---------|--------|---------|--------|-------|
| **Silence Detection** | ✅ RMS-based, sensitivity 0-100 | ✅ RMS-based, threshold -30 to -80 dBFS | TIE | Both excellent |
| **Takes Detection** | ✅ AI-powered, speech protection | ❌ Not detected | SPLICE | Unique to SPLICE |
| **Filler Word Removal** | ⚠️ Basic pattern matching | ✅ OpenAI Whisper, word-level | FireCut | FireCut more accurate |
| **J-Cuts/L-Cuts** | ✅ Lead-in/out timing (0.3/0.2s) | ❌ Not detected | SPLICE | Podcast-specific |
| **Profanity Detection** | ✅ Multi-language, custom blocklist | ✅ Similar implementation | TIE | Both complete |
| **Undo/Redo** | ⚠️ Relies on Premiere's undo | ✅ State save/restore via project export | FireCut | FireCut more robust |
| **Batch Processing** | ✅ Queue-based jobs | ❌ Not detected | SPLICE | Multiple files |

**SPLICE Advantages**:
- Takes detection (repeated recording segments)
- J-cuts for podcast workflows
- Multitrack speaker analysis
- Batch processing queue

**FireCut Advantages**:
- More accurate filler word detection (ML-based)
- Comprehensive undo system with state save

