### 7. Architecture & Code Quality

| Metric | SPLICE | FireCut | Winner |
|--------|--------|---------|--------|
| **Code Style** | Clean, readable, modern ES6+ | Heavily obfuscated, string concatenation | SPLICE |
| **Lines of Code** | 16,102 lines (UXP) | ~500KB minified | N/A |
| **Obfuscation** | None | Extensive (all 40 files) | SPLICE |
| **Comments** | Minimal but clear | Obfuscated away | SPLICE |
| **Module Pattern** | State + UI + functions per module | Obfuscated modules | SPLICE |
| **Error Handling** | Try-catch with user feedback | Try-catch throughout | TIE |
| **Async/Await** | Throughout | Throughout | TIE |
| **Security** | JWT + CSRF + server validation | Client-side license checks | SPLICE |
| **Backend** | Railway + PostgreSQL + Redis | firecut.ai backend | SPLICE |
| **Testing** | E2E tests, simulation mode | Unknown (code obfuscated) | SPLICE |

**SPLICE Advantages**:
- Clean, maintainable code (no obfuscation)
- Modern architecture (Railway, PostgreSQL, Redis)
- Server-side security (JWT, CSRF, token blacklist)
- E2E testing infrastructure
- TypeScript-ready codebase

**FireCut Advantages**:
- Obfuscation provides basic IP protection
- Mature, battle-tested in production

